# Current architecture (as-built, not aspirational)

`claude/ARCHITECTURE.md` describes a target layering: tRPC `server/routers`, a `services/` business-logic layer, and `functions/` Lambda consumers. **That layer does not exist in this codebase yet.** Do not create `server/` or `services/` folders or introduce tRPC unless the user explicitly asks for that migration. Build against the pattern actually in `src/` today:

- `src/app/(portal)/<area>/` — pages (Next.js App Router, server components). Keep thin: call feature functions, render the result. Areas today: dashboard, `account`, `clients` (CRM profiles), `materials` (Catalog: materials + recurring UI + import-export + consumables + equipment & tools), `pricing` (Rates: labor rates + complexity; index redirects to labor-rates), `settings` (permissions + users). Jobs/tickets/schedule were reverted 2026-07-19 (see `AGENTS.md` §2a); rebuild is piece by piece (quoting next), targeting one work-order entity — don't recreate the old `jobs`/`tickets` split.
- `src/features/<domain>/` — where real logic lives. Today: `materials` (catalog EAV + Excel IO + per-scope attribute CRUD + tax codes + capability-gated actions), `consumables` (division-scoped `ConsumableItem` CRUD; sell/labor derived — prompt 17), `equipment` (division-scoped `EquipmentItem` picklist placeholders; cost entered on quote/ticket, sell = cost × hard-baked 1.15 — prompt 18), `pricing` (labor rate cards + complexity multipliers + recurring fees/SMA + Cabin service plans + pure engines + Zod; **labor rates are base-driven, prompt 16**: position `baseHourlyRate` + the scope's `LaborRateConfig` multipliers are authoritative, Cost/Std/AH/Holiday/Discounted are derived via the single `recomputeRates` in `recompute.ts` and persisted as a materialized cache on every base/multiplier save — engines read the stored columns, admin UI edits Base only), `crm` (Customer → BillingProfile → Contacts → ServiceLocations — prompt 20), `scope` (active-scope context, prompt 15: `sps_active_scope` cookie + URL `?divisionId=&segment=`, `getActiveScope`, `ActiveScopeBar`), `settings` (role capability matrix + user overrides), `accounting` (schema-guard), `auth`, `cron`, `ingress`. **Three independent scopes** (prompt 14): IS Commercial (`IS_COM`), IS Residential (`IS_RES`), Cabin Services (`CS_STR`, single scope) — each owns its own materials, attributes, labor rates, complexity multipliers, and recurring/service pricing; nothing is shared or aliased across scopes. Each domain generally holds:
  - `actions.ts` — `"use server"` Server Actions. Pattern: auth/permission check first (`requireUser` / `requireArea` / `requireCapability` from `src/lib/session.ts`), then `schema.parse(raw)`, then the Prisma call, then `revalidatePath(...)` for every affected route.
  - `schemas.ts` — Zod schemas (Zod 4) for input validation, shared between the action and any client form.
  - `components/` — feature-specific UI.
- `src/lib/` — infra clients and cross-cutting helpers: `prisma.ts` (ops DB client), `prisma-pii.ts` (PII DB client), `auth.ts` (Better Auth config), `session.ts` (session + permission helpers), `device-surface.ts` / `get-server-surface.ts` / `require-desktop.ts` (desktop vs. mobile routing; `/materials`, `/pricing`, `/clients`, `/settings` are desktop-only).
- `src/config/` — `company.ts` (company/division/feature-flag source of truth; Cabin Services is one scope, `segments: ["str"]` — no shared-catalog aliasing) and `permissions.ts` (roles + area access rules; includes `materials`, `pricing`, `crm`). Nav: Operations = Dashboard + Clients + Catalog + Rates (`src/config/nav.ts`); section chrome via `SectionTabs` in `materials/layout.tsx` and `pricing/layout.tsx`, each rendering the one `ActiveScopeBar` below the tabs (prompt 15) — no page-level scope bars. Active scope resolves URL `?divisionId=&segment=` → `sps_active_scope` cookie → IS-Commercial (`src/features/scope/`, pages call `getActiveScope(searchParams)`); every materials list/count query is scope-filtered (units stay global), detail pages redirect the URL scope to the record's scope, create forms default to the active scope. Scope pickers: `ScopeSelector` + `resolveScope` (`src/features/materials/scope.ts`; validates the division + segment pair and returns segment + scope code — no separate storage segment).
- `src/proxy.ts` — the edge auth gate (this codebase's equivalent of `middleware.ts`): redirects unauthenticated requests to `/sign-in`, restricts `/api/v1/leads` to POST. Update `PUBLIC_PREFIXES` here when adding a new unauthenticated route. Authenticated APIs such as `/api/materials/export` stay off that list.
- `src/components/ui/` — shared UI primitives (shadcn/Radix/Base UI style), including accessible `select.tsx` for scope dropdowns.
- `src/components/patterns/` — `PageHeader`, `Panel`, `DataTableShell`, `SectionTabs`, `ScopeSelector`, etc. Portal content width is one `max-w-7xl` column in `PortalShell`.

When `claude/ARCHITECTURE.md` and the actual code disagree, follow the code. If a change would require reconciling the two, say so to the user rather than silently reintroducing the tRPC/services plan.
